data.message:
Ashraf Abdel Aleem
First of all, I NEVER USED A FRAMEWORK (or even a CMS !). But I like Laravel. 

Since I started coding with PHP (that was 7+ years ago), I was never comfortable using someone else 's code, so I never bothered to learn to use a framework or a CMS. I always loved writing everything from scratch.

My first framework (I named it "Unique") was very simple and lightweight, I loved it so much and decided to use it and work more on it, hoping that someday I could open-source it and share it with the world.

After 3 years of development and about 10+ projects it became more sophisticated and elegant, I named it "Zonda".

Nowadays, it's more awesome than ever. And it's called "Rhino", it's basically an HMVC, but instead of the Model part I use something that I call "DB Handlers", and instead of the View i use "Widgets". 

Rhino is so unbelievably fast, lightweight and secure. And it was intended to build Web Apps, not websites. I love this thing sooo much, here are some code sample:

$clients = DB_Clients::whereNameLike(' ... ')->orderByName()->limit(10)->get(['name', 'website']);

Database\Connections::get('master')->databases();

DB_clients::backup();

$dir = new Files\Directory( ... );
$dir->files(['php', 'psd'])->delete()->backup();

Plus so much more ...
